  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      -  Primary Objective:

           o To assess the efficacy of the probiotics in reducing the duration of diarrhea in
           children suffering from acute gastroenteritis.

        -  Secondary Objectives:

             -  To assess the efficacy of the probiotics in improving the frequency and consistency
                of stools.

             -  To assess the efficacy of the probiotics in avoiding recurrence of diarrhea.

             -  To assess the efficacy of the probiotics on the disease severity.

             -  To assess the safety and tolerability of the studied probiotics.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
